text:
First let me stress- I've been to other Moxy's and have always had a great experience! I'm a local who had an event to attend which I knew would run pretty late in area so instead of traveling home via the hectic subway, I treated myself to a overnight in the city. 
It was all downhill from the jump:
Long wait to check in;
Distracted, not so friend desk staff;
You have to take two sets of elevators to your room (that take FOREVER) using keycard for 2nd elevator-my cards were set up improperly, had to go back downstairs;
Room was never cleaned and missing bathsoap, handsoap, face towels, toilet paper-bathroom floors and sink area were filthy;
Sink was clogged; called front desk (no answer),took them 45 mins to send someone after I went down to get help (they didn't answer when I called the entire time mind you);
TV wasnt working;
Went down to inquire about room switch and they wouldnt accommodate (3rd trip downstairs);
AC unit is SO LOUD, it was torturous trying to fall asleep;
Right when I began to nod off- potent AF weed smells start seeping into the room at 130am in the morning!! Inconsiderate room neighbors-call downstairs, guess what? UNANSWERED.
To top it all off check out is at 11am, at 10am we had this rude maid (prob same that failed to prep our room) come knocking at the door asking when we were leaving- ARE YOU KIDDING ME?!

Overall terrible experience and I will be rethinking booking another Moxy in the future. This review may sounds bratty but when you try to treat yourself to a not so cheap staycation to then be stressed out with utter BS- its infuriating! 

If you are visiting NYC for the first time-

STEER CLEAR, YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED!
